The paper deals with network traffic classification using deep learning, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Convolutional Recurrent Neural Networks (CRNN) and Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the challenges of imbalanced datasets, which could also place it in the category of computational complexity (cs.CR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
